0visit%20to%20Chuck%20Close's%20gallery%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20artist's%20face%20blindness%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20one%20family%20rejected%20an%20admission%20offer%2C%20an%20Avenues%20cofounder%2C%20Alan%20Greenberg%2C%20wrote%20a%20letter%20urging%20them%20to%20reconsider.%20Greenberg%20wrote%20that%20Avenues%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20important%20new%20school%20ever%20opened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20in%20any%20way%20mean%20this%20to%20be%20demeaning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%20in%20an%20excerpt%20of%20the%20letter%20that%20was%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fcityroom.blogs.nytimes.com%2F2011%2F08%2F23%2Fa-new-private-school-doesnt-take-rejection-easily%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20would%20not%20be%20forthcoming%20or%20truthful%20if%20I%20did%20not%20say%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20comparison.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20tricycles%20in%20a%20walled%20courtyard%20of%20Avenues%3A%20The%20World%20School%2C%20with%20the%20Empire%20State%20Building%20seen%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675a06bb91c1cc343d47f1a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClose%20to%202%2C000%20students%20are%20enrolled%20at%20Avenues'%20Chelsea%20campus.%3Cp%3EAmir%20Hamja%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThirteen%20years%20later%2C%20Avenues%20has%20had%20seven%20different%20heads%20of%20school%2C%20including%20one%20whose%20tenure%20lasted%20two%20months.%20After%20once%20talking%20of%20building%2020%20campuses%20around%20the%20world%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20with%20three.%20In%20November%202023%2C%20the%20school's%20two%20profitable%20campuses%2C%20Manhattan%20and%20S%C3%A3o%20Paulo%2C%20were%20sold%20to%20Nord%20Anglia%20Education%2C%20a%20private-equity-backed%20chain%20of%20for-profit%20international%20boarding%20schools.%20It%20was%20the%20third%20time%20the%20school%20had%20been%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20parents%20sang%20Avenues'%20praises%2C%20many%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they'd%20been%20disappointed%20by%20what%20they%20had%20come%20to%20view%20as%20essentially%20an%20educational%20experiment%20gone%20awry.%20They%20said%20the%20focus%20on%20dual-language%20learning%20came%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20core%20subjects.%20Parents%20of%20older%20students%20lamented%20what%20they%20viewed%20as%20a%20lack%20of%20structure%20and%20said%20kids%20weren't%20penalized%20for%20not%20doing%20their%20homework.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20kids%20are%20kind%20of%20like%20the%20guinea%20pigs%20for%20this%20growth%20model%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20mom%20who%20enrolled%20her%202-year-old%20son%20at%20Avenues%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20In%202023%2C%20after%20four%20years%20at%20the%20school%2C%20she%20pulled%20him%20out.%20Having%20him%20learn%20Mandarin%20without%20a%20native-speaking%20nanny%20or%20heavy%20tutoring%20was%20increasingly%20unfeasible%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20close%20to%202%2C000%20students%20are%20enrolled%20at%20Avenues'%20Chelsea%20campus%2C%20where%20tuition%20for%20nursery%20school%20starts%20at%20%2468%2C850%20%E2%80%94%20among%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues'%20head%20of%20school%2C%20Todd%20Shy%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20thousands%20of%20happy%2C%20satisfied%20families%20and%20thriving%20students.%20Avenues%20is%20an%20innovative%20school%20that%20achieves%20exceptional%20student%20outcomes%20using%20research-backed%20practices.%26quot%3B%20An%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20in%20the%20school's%20annual%20%26quot%3Bvoice%20of%20the%20community%26quot%3B%20survey%2C%2090%25%20of%20parents%20%26quot%3Bagreed%20that%20Avenues%20is%20an%20enjoyable%20school%20for%20their%20family%26quot%3B%20and%20more%20than%2090%25%20were%20happy%20with%20the%20college%20their%20child%20ultimately%20attended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Whittle%2C%20an%20Avenues%20cofounder%20and%20former%20CEO%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Breally%20proud%20of%20how%20the%20school%20has%20done.%26quot%3B%20But%20some%20people%20said%20Avenues%20had%20failed%20to%20achieve%20an%20impossible%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20for-profit%20school%20with%20great%20tech%20support%20and%20dual-language%20programs%20seems%20pretty%20sexy%2C%26quot%3B%20Wendy%20Levey%2C%20an%20admissions%20consultant%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20people%20are%20going%20to%20spend%20that%20kind%20of%20money%2C%20they%20want%20faculty%20that%20have%20been%20in%20place%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20a%20curriculum%20that%20has%20been%20proven%20to%20work%2C%20alumni%20who%20are%20attached%20to%20the%20school.%20They%20want%20the%20whole%20nine%20yards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20they%20want%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bclub%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20loosely%20affiliated%20network%20of%20girls%2C%20boys%2C%20and%20co-ed%20schools%20that%20make%20up%20the%20city's%20educational%20elite.%20%26quot%3BEven%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Levey%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BAvenues%20is%20not%20part%20of%20that%20club.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20New%20York%20City%20parent%20in%20a%20certain%20income%20bracket%20who%20has%20deemed%20public%20school%20a%20nonstarter%2C%20chances%20are%20you're%20familiar%20with%20the%20hellscape%20that%20is%20trying%20to%20get%20your%20kid%20into%20private%20school.%20The%20search%20for%20a%20competitive%20preschool%20often%20starts%20when%20your%20child%20is%20just%20a%20year%20old.%20By%20the%20time%20you%20get%20to%20primary%20school%2C%20it%20seems%20as%20though%20all%20but%20one%20open%20spot%20is%20reserved%20for%20siblings%20and%20legacies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20manage%20to%20land%20at%20Horace%20Mann%2C%20Spence%2C%20or%20one%20of%20the%20other%20elite%20nonprofit%20private%20schools%20that%20some%20admissions%20professionals%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Bbig%2020%2C%26quot%3B%20you're%20so%20grateful%20that%20you%20tolerate%20the%20incessant%20fundraising%20emails%20for%20the%20early-learning%20center%20that%20won't%20be%20built%20until%20your%20child%20is%20too%20old%20to%20use%20it.%20You%20tell%20yourself%20that%20the%20dingy%20basement%20where%20you%20deposit%20your%20toddler%20each%20morning%20is%20quaint%2C%20cozy%2C%20and%20traditional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20increasingly%20high-end%20city%2C%20private%20school%20remains%20a%20remarkably%20spartan%20affair.%20If%20there%20are%20elevators%20on%20campus%2C%20students%20are%20often%20forbidden%20to%20use%20them%20until%20senior%20year.%20Children%20served%20by%20macrobiotic%20chefs%20at%20their%20Hamptons%20summer%20homes%20push%20beat-up%20plastic%20trays%20down%20a%20poorly%20lit%20cafeteria%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20amid%20this%20landscape%20that%20Avenues%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene.%20Whittle%2C%20a%20former%20Esquire%20publisher%20who'd%20turned%20%E2%80%94%20somewhat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.vanityfair.com%2Farticle%2F1990%2F3%2Fis-chris-whittle-the-devil%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtroversially%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20for-profit%20education%2C%20imagined%20a%20sleek%2C%20newfangled%20school%20with%20a%20global%20mindset.%20Graduates%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bartists%20no%20matter%20their%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bat%20ease%20beyond%20borders%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Barchitects%20of%20lives%20that%20ascend%20the%20ordinary%2C%26quot%3B%20Avenues'%20mission%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhittle%20and%20his%20two%20cofounders%20%E2%80%94%20Benno%20Schmidt%2C%20a%20former%20Yale%20president%2C%20and%20Greenberg%2C%20who%20used%20to%20be%20the%20publisher%20of%20Esquire%20%E2%80%94%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20money%20selling%20their%20idea.%20Avenues%20hired%20a%20marketing%20team%20that%20included%20an%20MTV%20animator%20and%20Ken%20Segall%2C%20who%20conceived%20of%20Apple's%20famous%20%26quot%3BThink%20Different%26quot%3B%20campaign.%20They%20sent%20a%20direct-mailer%20brick%20to%201%2C000%20New%20York%20City%20parents%20and%20threw%20swanky%20cocktail%20parties%20at%20the%20Crosby%20Street%20Hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20parents%20who%20snickered%20at%20the%20school's%20tactics%20showed%20up%20to%20see%20what%20all%20the%20fuss%20was%20about.%20%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20was%2C%20let's%20make%20it%20feel%20like%20we've%20been%20there%20forever%20and%20you%20just%20found%20out%20about%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Avenues%20global%20creative%20director%20Andy%20Clayman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhittle%20had%20made%20a%20career%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecommoditizing%20education.%20In%20the%201990s%2C%20he%20conceived%20of%20The%20Edison%20Project%2C%20a%20network%20of%20commercial%20private%20schools%20that%20eventually%20transitioned%20into%20managing%20low-income%20public%20schools%20in%20cities%20such%20as%20Baltimore%20and%20Philadelphia.%20In%202003%2C%20Liberty%20Partners%20bought%20The%20Edison%20Project%20for%20%24174%20million.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20Liberty%20sold%20the%20company%2C%20reportedly%20taking%20an%2085%25%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20embodied%20the%20same%20premise%20as%20Edison%3A%20namely%2C%20that%20innovative%20business%20people%20could%20educate%20students%20better%20than%20traditional%20nonprofit%20schools.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20this%20was%20a%20welcome%20philosophy%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20During%20Mike%20Bloomberg's%2012%20years%20as%20mayor%2C%20nearly%20200%20%26quot%3Blow-performing%26quot%3B%20public%20schools%20were%20closed%2C%20replaced%20by%20150%20privately%20operated%2C%20publicly%20funded%20charter%20schools.%20As%20much%20as%2040%25%20of%20the%20city%20was%20rezoned%20to%20accommodate%20mixed-use%20development%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20Avenues'%20flagship%20campus%20in%20a%20converted%20industrial%20building%20sandwiched%20between%20public%20housing%20and%20the%20High%20Line%2C%20the%20elevated%20park%20that%20runs%20through%20Manhattan's%20Chelsea%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues'%20for-profit%20status%20was%20appealing%20to%20what%20one%20Avenues%20parent%2C%20Euan%20Rellie%2C%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20kind%20of%20Bloombergian%20New%20Yorker.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20imagine%20if%20you're%20an%20entrepreneur%20or%20private-equity%20guy%2C%20you%20might%20say%2C%20good%2C%20there's%20less%20bullshit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rellie%2C%20who%20cofounded%20the%20private-equity%20firm%20BDA%20Partners.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20a%20straightforward%20service%20provider.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESejal%20Shah%20enrolled%20both%20her%20daughters%20after%20touring%20the%20school%20in%202012.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seemed%20like%20a%20place%20to%20move%20and%20grow%20versus%20being%20stagnant%20in%20one%20way%20of%20thinking%20and%20one%20way%20of%20doing%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues'%20timing%20couldn't%20have%20been%20better.%20From%202006%20to%202011%2C%20the%20number%20of%20kids%20younger%20than%205%20in%20Manhattan%20had%20increased%20by%2032%25%2C%20Whittle%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2011%2F07%2F10%2Fnyregion%2Fthe-best-school-75-million-can-buy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20only%20about%20400%20spots%20at%20top%20independent%20schools%20had%20emerged%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20According%20to%20the%20Times%2C%20by%20June%202011%2C%201%2C200%20families%20had%20applied%20for%20early%20admission%20to%20Avenues%2C%20even%20though%20just%20eight%20of%20180%20teachers%20had%20been%20hired%2C%20the%20building%20was%20a%20construction%20site%2C%20and%20the%20curriculum%20was%20still%20a%20giant%20question%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20hired%20academic%20heavy%20hitters%20like%20Nancy%20Schulman%2C%20the%20former%20director%20of%20the%2092nd%20Street%20Y%20preschool%2C%20one%20of%20the%20city's%20most%20prestigious%20private-school%20feeders%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20former%20Dalton%20headmaster%2C%20Gardner%20P.%20Dunnan.%20Still%2C%20Whittle%20made%20clear%20that%20he%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20being%20another%20Dalton.%20%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20the%20biggest%20risk%20is%20that%20we%20are%20just%20another%20fine%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fobserver.com%2F2012%2F06%2Fhas-avenues-mastermind-chris-whittle-learned-his-lesson%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Observer%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202012.%20%26quot%3BIf%20that's%20all%20we%20are%2C%20this%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhittle's%20run%20at%20Avenues%20was%20relatively%20short-lived.%20In%202013%2C%20John%20Fisher%20%E2%80%94%20the%20conservative%20Gap%20Inc.%20heir%20whose%20family%20gave%20The%20Edison%20Project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfgate.com%2Fnews%2Farticle%2FWEALTH-POWER-AND-VISION-Gap-founder-Don-Fisher-2548718.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2425%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20who%20was%20an%20early%20minority%20investor%20in%20Avenues%20%E2%80%94%20bought%20out%20one%20of%20the%20school's%20two%20main%20backers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20hostile%20takeover%20in%20that%20I%20fought%20it%2C%20and%20I%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Whittle%2C%20who%20also%20placed%20a%20bid%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFisher%20tapped%20Jeff%20Clark%20as%20the%20new%20president%20of%20Avenues%20in%20November%202013%2C%20the%20change%20briefly%20mentioned%20at%20the%20end%20of%20Whittle's%20annual%20newsletter.%20The%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20school%20didn't%20make%20a%20big%20deal%20about%20the%20appointment%20to%20parents%20because%20it%20%26quot%3Bin%20no%20way%20impacted%20day-to-day%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chris%20Whittle%20walking%20up%20a%20spiral%20staircase%20in%20front%20of%20a%20glass%20block%20wall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675a07b252dd0818d1a688ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222403%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChristopher%20Whittle%2C%20an%20Avenues%20cofounder%2C%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20he%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20starting%20another%20Dalton.%20%26quot%3BIf%20that's%20all%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%202012%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESarah%20L.%20Voisin%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20year%2C%20the%20school's%20parent%20company%2C%20Avenues%20Global%20Holdings%2C%20loaned%20Whittle%20almost%20%2411%20million%20that%20a%202018%20legal%20document%20said%20was%20meant%20to%20%26quot%3Bameliorate%20his%20dire%20personal%20financial%20situation%20so%20he%20could%20focus%20on%20his%20work%20for%20Avenues.%26quot%3B%20(A%20person%20close%20to%20the%20company%20said%20the%20loans%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20purported%20financial%20struggles.)%20Whittle%20got%20an%20additional%20%241%20million%20in%202014%2C%20but%20he%20ultimately%20failed%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202015%2C%20Whittle%20left%20the%20school.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20sued%20him%20and%20foreclosed%20on%20his%20Hamptons%20home.%20In%202018%2C%20Fisher%20bought%20out%20the%20last%20minority%20investor%2C%20gaining%20full%20control%20of%20Avenues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20typical%20New%20York%20City%20private%20school%20grows%20incrementally.%20Nightingale%2C%20Spence%2C%20and%20Chapin%20began%20in%20Manhattan%20brownstones%20and%20expanded%20over%20decades%2C%20one%20capital%20campaign%20and%20Ivy%20League%20acceptance%20at%20a%20time.%20Whittle%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20raised%20%2475%20million%20to%20renovate%20Avenues'%20Chelsea%20campus%20in%20just%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20facility%20embodied%20Whittle's%20idea%20of%20education%20as%20a%20luxury%20good.%20The%20cafeteria%20is%20named%20%26quot%3BFOOD%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20SoHo%20restaurant%20founded%20by%20the%20artist%20Gordon%20Matta-Clark%2C%20and%20Avenues%20students%20in%20first%20through%20fifth%20grade%20receive%20iPads%20to%20do%20their%20schoolwork.%20There%20is%20no%20central%20library%3B%20Whittle%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2Favenues-school-chris-whittle-2012-9%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202012%20that%20his%20eventual%20goal%20was%20to%20have%20a%20paperless%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20parents%20were%20drawn%20to%20Avenues'%20modern%20approach%20to%20elite%20academia.%20Instead%20of%20the%20pinafores%20and%20khakis%20favored%20by%20private%20institutions%20like%20Brearley%20or%20Collegiate%2C%20students%20wear%20a%20mix%20of%20gray%2C%20black%2C%20or%20white%20solids.%20There's%20an%20emphasis%20on%20boardroom-style%20presentations%20and%20group%20projects%2C%20rather%20than%20teacher-led%20lectures%2C%20essays%2C%20or%20written%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20attended%20the%20first%20year%2C%20you%20drank%20the%20Kool-Aid%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20mother%20who%20enrolled%20her%204-year-old%20son%20at%20Avenues%20in%202012.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20you%20choose%20an%20unknown%20entity%20for%20top%20dollar%20with%20no%20proven%20track%20record%3F%20You%20had%20to%20believe%20in%20something%20bigger.%26quot%3B%20Another%20mother%2C%20who%20transferred%20her%20daughter%20out%20of%20Avenues%20in%202023%20after%20her%20freshman%20year%2C%20called%20the%20early%20years%20there%20%26quot%3Bmagical%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20kids%20would%20run%20with%20smiles%20into%20school.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20school's%20biggest%20academic%20selling%20point%20has%20always%20been%20its%20language%20immersion%20program.%20Originally%2C%202-year-olds%20at%20Avenues%20were%20taught%20in%20a%20combination%20of%20English%2C%20Spanish%2C%20and%20Mandarin.%20When%20students%20entered%20the%20threes%20program%2C%20they%20chose%20Mandarin%20or%20Spanish%20as%20their%20target%20language%20and%20spent%20half%20their%20time%20learning%20in%20that%20language.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20instance%2C%20after%20a%20bilingual%20morning%20meeting%2C%20students%20might%20do%20a%20small-group%20reading%20in%20Mandarin%2C%20followed%20by%20another%20learning%20period%20in%20English.%20Science%20would%20then%20be%20in%20English%2C%20with%20music%20and%20art%20taught%20in%20Mandarin.%20(Beginning%20next%20year%2C%20based%20on%20parent%20feedback%2C%20kids%20will%20choose%20a%20target%20language%20at%20age%201%2C%20the%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20said.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20first%20through%20fifth%20grades%2C%20subjects%20like%20language%20arts%20and%20math%20switch%20between%20English%20and%20Spanish%20or%20Mandarin%20on%20alternating%20days.%20By%20sixth%20grade%2C%20the%20dual-language%20component%20tapers%20off%20because%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20students%20are%20highly%20proficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20bilingual%20program%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20more%20than%20they'd%20bargained%20for.%20One%20mother%20told%20BI%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20her%20son's%20first%20year%20in%20Avenues'%20twos%20program%20in%202019%2C%20she%20began%20receiving%20feedback%20from%20the%20school%20that%20he%20needed%20additional%20support%20to%20learn%20Mandarin.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20telling%20us%20to%20get%20him%20a%20tutor%20and%20potentially%20a%20Mandarin-speaking%20babysitter%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20started%20realizing%20that%20it's%20not%20practically%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20the%20mother%20said%2C%20Avenues%20suggested%20that%20she%20take%20her%20son%20to%20occupational%20therapy%20for%20behavioral%20issues%20that%20she%20felt%20stemmed%20from%20the%20immersion%20program's%20rigor.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20felt%20like%20we%20had%20to%20outsource%20everything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Last%20year%2C%20she%20transferred%20her%20son%20to%20a%20traditional%20nonprofit%20school%20for%20first%20grade%20where%20she%20said%20he's%20thriving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20some%20families%20may%20choose%20additional%20support%20outside%20of%20school%2C%20this%20is%20not%20required%20nor%20expected%20at%20Avenues%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20discouraged%20in%20early%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rows%20of%20tables%20and%20chairs%20in%20the%20Avenues%20cafeteria.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675a06ef91c1cc343d47f1bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cafeteria%20at%20Avenues'%20Chelsea%20campus%20is%20named%20%26quot%3BFOOD%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20SoHo%20restaurant%20founded%20by%20the%20artist%20Gordon%20Matta-Clark.%3Cp%3EAmir%20Hamja%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mother%20who%20enrolled%20her%204-year-old%20son%20at%20Avenues%20the%20year%20it%20opened%20said%20she%20started%20noticing%20in%20elementary%20school%20that%20her%20son's%20basic%20reading%20and%20writing%20skills%20paled%20in%20comparison%20with%20his%20Mandarin.%20She%20also%20became%20exceedingly%20frustrated%20that%20he%20completed%20assignments%20mainly%20on%20his%20school-provided%20iPad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20the%20hype%20around%20Avenues%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20just%20not%20impressed%20with%20it%20as%20an%20academic%20institution%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mom%20said.%20She%20decided%20to%20transfer%20her%20son%20out%20for%20eighth%20grade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20learning%20in%20two%20languages%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20detract%20from%20what%20children%20need%20developmentally%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20school's%20language%20immersion%20program%20had%20%26quot%3Bbeen%20designed%20to%20maintain%20literacy%20development.%26quot%3B%20The%20spokesperson%20separately%20said%20that%20Avenues%20graduates%20were%20%26quot%3Bthriving%20at%20leading%20colleges%20and%20universities.%26quot%3B%20From%202016%20to%202024%2C%20four%20went%20on%20to%20attend%20Harvard%2C%20four%20went%20to%20Yale%2C%20and%20one%20student%20attended%20Princeton%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.avenues.org%2Fabout%2Fcollege-counseling%2Fmatriculation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAvenues'%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20parents%20or%20even%20teachers%20are%20convinced%20of%20the%20efficacy%20of%20Avenues'%20methods.%20One%20teacher%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20Chelsea%20school%20for%20a%20year%20prior%20to%20COVID%20said%20she%20noticed%20a%20skills%20gap%20between%20her%20Avenues%20lower-school%20students%20and%20those%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20private%20school%20where%20she%20now%20teaches.%20She%20believed%20Avenues%20students'%20writing%20suffered%20because%20they%20learned%20in%20English%20only%20half%20the%20time.%20The%20Avenues%20spokesperson%20said%20they%20did%20not%20recognize%20the%20teacher's%20characterization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20former%20Avenues%20parents%20also%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20they%20bought%20into%20the%20school's%20modernistic%20approach%20to%20education%2C%20they%20grew%20concerned%20that%20it%20was%20becoming%20too%20loose.%20One%20mother%20said%20that%20when%20her%20daughter%20entered%20middle%20school%20in%202019%2C%20Avenues%20%26quot%3Btried%20to%20teach%20math%20three%20different%20ways%20at%20one%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20confusing%20her%20preteen%2C%20who%20didn't%20know%20which%20method%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mother%20who%20transferred%20her%20daughter%20out%20of%20Avenues%20during%20high%20school%20expressed%20similar%20reservations.%20She%20told%20BI%20that%20in%20middle%20school%2C%20her%20daughter%20was%20surprised%20to%20learn%20from%20a%20friend%20at%20an%20uptown%20private%20school%20that%20they%20got%20in%20trouble%20for%20not%20doing%20their%20homework.%20There%20was%20so%20little%20communication%20between%20parents%20and%20teachers%2C%20the%20mother%20said%2C%20that%20one%20year%20she%20didn't%20learn%20her%20daughter%20was%20struggling%20academically%20until%20January.%20(The%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20if%20a%20student%20doesn't%20complete%20their%20homework%2C%20a%20teacher%20might%20pull%20them%20aside%20to%20%26quot%3Btalk%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20personal%20accountability.%26quot%3B%20The%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bstudent%20progress%20is%20carefully%20monitored%20through%20regular%20formal%20and%20informal%20assessments%26quot%3B%20that%20are%20reported%20to%20and%20discussed%20with%20parents.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20school%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20lauded%2C%20can%20be%20perfect%20for%20every%20student.%20One%20mother%20recently%20transferred%20her%20daughter%20from%20Avenues%20to%20a%20more%20traditional%20private%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eschool%20for%20sixth%20grade.%20While%20at%20Avenues%2C%20she'd%20suspected%20her%20daughter%20might%20be%20behind%20her%20peers%20at%20other%20private%20schools%2C%20but%20she%20was%20willing%20to%20make%20the%20trade-off%20for%20a%20kid%20who%20was%20fluent%20in%20Spanish%2C%20tech-savvy%2C%20and%20a%20confident%20public%20speaker.%20%26quot%3BThen%20I%20came%20here%2C%20and%20she%20was%20literally%20almost%20three%20years%20behind%20in%20math%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mom%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20English%2C%20she%20was%20getting%20tested%20on%20adverbs%20and%20pronouns%2C%20and%20she%20knew%20none%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20%26quot%3Breally%20honed%20in%20on%20skills%20that%20you%20need%20for%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mother%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20not%20the%20basics%20of%20education.%20But%20who%20knows%20if%20the%20basics%20of%20education%20are%20even%20necessary%2010%20years%20from%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20had%20always%20planned%20to%20build%20a%20global%20network%20of%20schools%2C%20a%20former%20administrator%20told%20BI%2C%20pointing%20to%20its%20robust%20research%20and%20development%20team%2C%20which%20totaled%2030%20full-%20and%20part-time%20staffers%20by%202019.%20But%20in%20the%20end%2C%20Avenues%20ended%20up%20with%20only%20three%20campuses%3A%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China%3B%20Sao%20P%C3%A3olo%2C%20Brazil%3B%20and%20New%20York%20City.%20A%20temporary%20Silicon%20Valley%20location%20served%2070%20students%20during%20the%202022-2023%20school%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Fisher%20decided%20to%20sell%20the%20business%2C%20the%20goal%20was%20to%20find%20a%20buyer%20to%20purchase%20the%20whole%20thing.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20didn't%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20administrator%20said.%20%26quot%3BDid%20they%20make%20mistakes%3F%20Hell%20yeah%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btheir%20mistakes%20cost%20them%20their%20vision%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20former%20administrator%20called%20the%20dissolution%20of%20that%20vision%20%26quot%3Bheartbreaking%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20believes%20the%20new%20ownership%20will%20bring%20%26quot%3Breal%20stability.%26quot%3B%20A%20Nord%20Anglia%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20group%20chose%20to%20purchase%20Avenues'%20Chelsea%20and%20S%C3%A3o%20Paulo%20campuses%20in%20part%20because%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bclose%20cultural%20fit%20between%20us%20as%20educators.%26quot%3B%20Plans%20to%20build%20a%20permanent%20Silicon%20Valley%20location%20were%20scrapped%20after%20the%20Nord%20Anglia%20acquisition%2C%20and%20Avenues%20Shenzhen%20is%20now%20independently%20owned%20and%20operated%20by%20a%20local%20partner%20in%20China%2C%20which%20licenses%20the%20Avenues%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20did%20have%20some%20parents%20reach%20out%20to%20me%20after%20the%20sale%2C%26quot%3B%20Whittle%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20overall%2C%20it%20is%20going%20to%20be%20quite%20good%20for%20Avenues.%20They're%20a%20capable%2C%20thoughtful%20group.%20They%20have%20global%20reach%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20important%20to%20the%20student%20body.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20Nord%20Anglia%20itself%20was%20sold%20to%20a%20new%20ownership%20group%2C%20which%20could%20theoretically%20shift%20things%20at%20Avenues%20again.%20Avenues'%20spokesperson%20said%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20changes%2C%20%26quot%3Bour%20focus%20has%20been%20%E2%80%94%20and%20always%20will%20be%20%E2%80%94%20on%20our%20students%20and%20providing%20a%20world-class%20education.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Avenues%20The%20World%20School%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675a072852dd0818d1a688ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20former%20Avenues%20administrator%20said%20she%20believed%20Nord%20Anglia's%20purchase%20of%20the%20Chelsea%20and%20Sao%20P%C3%A3olo%20campuses%20would%20bring%20the%20school%20%26quot%3Breal%20stability.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAmir%20Hamja%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20school%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20appeal%20to%20a%20broader%20swath%20of%20families.%20In%20the%20early%20days%2C%20students%20hoping%20to%20transfer%20into%20Avenues%20from%20first%20to%20fifth%20grade%20had%20to%20pass%20a%20Spanish%20or%20Mandarin%20competency%20exam.%20But%20in%202017%2C%20Avenues%20launched%20a%20pilot%20English-only%20program%20for%20incoming%20fifth%20graders%20that%20gradually%20expanded%20to%20include%20the%20third%20and%20fourth%20grades.%20This%20past%20school%20year%2C%2033%20students%20enrolled%20at%20Avenues%20were%20non-immersion%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20school%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20add%20more%20English-only%20lower-school%20spots%20if%20parents%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20parents%20see%20Avenues'%20flexibility%20as%20a%20plus.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20like%20change%2C%20Avenues%20is%20not%20the%20right%20place%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lynn%20Berney%2C%20who%20has%20two%20children%20in%20high%20school%20and%20one%20who%20recently%20graduated.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20do%20think%20that%20they're%20constantly%20improving%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERellie's%20younger%20son%2C%20who's%20now%20a%20senior%2C%20is%20staying%20put.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20the%20parent%20of%20a%20teenager%20is%20such%20an%20effing%20roller%20coaster%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Byou%20tend%20to%20muddle%20through%20until%20there's%20a%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20says%20its%20enrollment%20has%20remained%20consistent.%20The%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20applications%20to%20its%20New%20York%20campus%20increased%20by%2050%25%20from%20September%202018%20to%20September%202023%2C%20while%20the%20acceptance%20rate%20fell%20by%2018%25.%20They%20added%20that%202024's%20admissions%20rate%20was%20about%205%25%20lower%20than%202023's%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20indicates%20continued%20strong%20demand%20for%20limited%20seats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvenues%20may%20not%20have%20become%20exactly%20what%20Whittle%20imagined.%20Depending%20on%20whom%20you%20ask%2C%20it%20might%20not%20even%20be%20a%20particularly%20successful%20academic%20institution.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20consultant-created%20conceit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20mother%20whose%20son%20struggled%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20Mandarin%20component.%20%26quot%3BThe%20shots%20are%20called%20at%20corporate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20school%20succeeded%20in%20at%20least%20one%20way.%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20the%20impossible%20thing%3A%20We%20were%20profitable%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Clayman%2C%20the%20former%20Avenues%20global%20creative%20director.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20why%20we%20were%20bought.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favenues-nyc-private-school-sale-nord-anglia-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736159402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favenues-nyc-private-school-sale-nord-anglia-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20downtown%20for-profit%20school%20drew%20celebrity%20kids%20like%20Suri%20Cruise.%20But%20some%20say%20Avenues%20fell%20short%20on%20academics%20and%20its%20promise%20of%20a%20global%20campus.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lysandra%20Ohrstrom)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20worked%20at%20Boeing%20for%20over%2030%20years.%20I%20witnessed%20the%20fallout%20of%20outsourcing%20firsthand.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227639%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Boeing%20sign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665c8928d0b8e1c832cb117a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225093%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20Boeing%20engineer%20shares%20what%2030%20years%20at%20the%20beleaguered%20plane%20company%20was%20like.%3Cp%3EPATRICK%20T.%20FALLON%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EManufacturing%20engineer%20Douglas%20Dorsey%20started%20working%20at%20Boeing%20in%201984%20and%20retired%20in%202017.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDorsey%20worked%20on%20the%20Boeing%20777%20and%20787%20Dreamliner%2C%20where%20he%20said%20things%20began%20to%20unravel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20reflects%20on%20his%20time%20on%20the%20shop%20floor%20and%20how%20Boeing%20plans%20to%20repair%20its%20reputation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Douglas%20Dorsey%2C%20from%20Washington%2C%20about%20his%20career%20as%20a%20manufacturing%20engineer%20at%20Boeing.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20career%20at%20Boeing%20in%201984%2C%20and%20I%20worked%20there%20for%20over%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20manufacturing%20engineer.%20My%20responsibilities%20included%20writing%20instructions%20and%20coming%20up%20with%20assembly%20sequences%20for%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20career%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20several%20aircraft%20projects%20for%20Boeing%2C%20including%20the%20Advanced%20Tactical%20Fighter%20program%2C%20the%20Boeing%20777%2C%20and%20the%20787%20Dreamliner.%20It%20was%20always%20interesting%20and%20challenging.%20I%20worked%20with%20dedicated%20employees%20and%20on%20cutting-edge%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20retired%20in%202017%20feeling%20proud%20to%20have%20worked%20there.%20I%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Blifer%26quot%3B%20with%20Boeing%20blue%20blood%20running%20through%20my%20veins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20working%20on%20the%20Boeing%20787%20program%20in%20the%202000s%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20outsourcing%20manufacturing%20tasks%20to%20suppliers%20became%20a%20really%20big%20problem%20for%20Boeing.%20When%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20shop%20floor%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20negative%20impacts%20of%20outsourcing%20to%20suppliers%2C%20such%20as%20slower%20production%20and%20delivering%20incomplete%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20retiring%2C%20I've%20stayed%20up%20to%20date%20with%20Boeing.%20I've%20followed%20the%20news%20on%20malfunctions%20and%20strikes%2C%20but%20I%20think%20management%20is%20taking%20baby%20steps%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b6707b4-0d96-44df-8fd3-2593b002e519%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20saw%20chaos%20unfold%20at%20Boeing%20due%20to%20mismanagement%20and%20outsourcing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20good%20old%20days%2C%20I%20had%20a%20positive%20opinion%20of%20Boeing.%20In%20my%20first%20decade%20at%20the%20company%2C%20the%20chain%20of%20command%20was%20clear.%20You%20knew%20what%20your%20job%20responsibilities%20were%20and%20could%20count%20on%20your%20line%20managers.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20there%20was%20no%20drama%20with%20executives%2C%20and%20we%20had%20confidence%20in%20those%20in%20command.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%201997%2C%20upper%20management%20was%20thrown%20into%20chaos%20when%20Boeing%20merged%20with%20McDonnell%20Douglas%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fqz.com%2F1776080%2Fhow-the-mcdonnell-douglas-boeing-merger-led-to-the-737-max-crisis%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520the%2520eyes%2520of%2520many%2Cshareholders%2520of%2520the%2520merged%2520companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonnell%20Douglas%20executives%3C%2Fa%3E%20taking%20top%20positions%20at%20Boeing.%20Harry%20Stonecipher%2C%20who%20was%20briefly%20Boeing's%20CEO%2C%20resigned%20in%202005%20after%20he%20was%20found%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F2005%2F03%2F08%2Fboeing-ceo-resigns-over-affair-with-subordinate%2F199b6a6b-9883-457d-991b-ea23840b1fe2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20affair%20with%20an%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20like%20a%20corporate%20soap%20opera%20played%20out%20in%20the%20media.%20As%20an%20employee%2C%20the%20news%20was%20distracting%20and%20felt%20like%20evidence%20of%20the%20level%20of%20disorder%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Boeing%20787%20program%20was%20underway.%20The%20787%20was%20launched%20as%20a%20complete%20departure%20from%20how%20Boeing%20airplanes%20had%20traditionally%20been%20constructed.%20To%20reduce%20the%20time%20from%20program%20launch%20to%20when%20the%20planes%20were%20in%20service%2C%20Boeing%20would%20have%20%26quot%3Brisk-sharing%20partners%26quot%3B%20deliver%20complete%20aircraft%20sections%20to%20the%20final%20assembly%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E787%20program%20managers%20and%20employees%20implicitly%20understood%20this%20new%20production%20method%2C%20and%20we%20cautiously%20believed%20it%20might%20work.%20But%20it%20began%20to%20unravel%20bit%20by%20bit%20and%20ended%20in%20a%20three-year%20delay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220dce5b94-9329-4440-81d6-0bb4c80b9ef5%5C%22%3EI%20wondered%20why%20we%20were%20accepting%20substandard%20work%20on%20787%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20project%20manufacturing%20engineer%20for%20the%20787%2C%20creating%20work%20instructions%2C%20and%20a%20liaison%20manufacturing%20engineer%2C%20working%20on%20the%20shop%20floor%20to%20resolve%20issues%20with%20existing%20work%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20each%20new%20airplane%20program%2C%20program%20leadership%20and%20supply%20chain%20management%20divided%20major%20sections%20of%20the%20aircraft%20among%20various%20subcontractors%2C%20suppliers%2C%20and%20risk-sharing%20%26quot%3Bpartners.%26quot%3B%20When%20suppliers%20were%20late%20in%20delivering%20their%20components%20or%20delivered%20them%20incomplete%2C%20this%20became%20%26quot%3Btraveled%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20had%20to%20be%20completed%20by%20Boeing%20employees%20during%20final%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20much%20of%20my%20time%20on%20the%20program%20trying%20to%20accommodate%20parts%20that%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bnon-conformance%26quot%3B%20tag%20on%20them%20and%20had%20to%20be%20reworked%20and%20installed%20into%20the%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wondered%20what%20was%20going%20on%20and%20why%20we%20were%20accepting%20substandard%2C%20incomplete%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20engineer%2C%20I%20wasn't%20privy%20to%20the%20decisions%20going%20on%20in%20the%20upper%20chambers%20of%20management%2C%20but%20I%20could%20see%20the%20chaos%20filtering%20down.%20It%20felt%20like%20the%20company%20wasn't%20listening%20to%20its%20mechanics%20about%20how%20to%20improve%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20group%20meetings%20where%20employees%2C%20including%20myself%2C%20questioned%20decisions%20by%20management%20and%20offered%20constructive%20criticism%20that%20was%20politely%20but%20bluntly%20blown%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20787%20was%20sadly%20delayed%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f311f4c0-a156-4e3a-8f30-1b470303a27f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConfusing%20supply%20chains%20seem%20to%20still%20cause%20problems%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20there%20was%20an%20incident%20with%20a%20Boeing%20737%20Max%20plane%2C%20where%20a%20door%20plug%20blew%20out%20after%20take%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20retired%20in%202017%2C%20I%20think%20this%20was%20caused%20by%20mismanagement%20of%20traveled%20repair%20work.%20The%20plug%20door%20was%20manufactured%20by%20Spirit%20AeroSystems%2C%20a%20Boeing%20subsidiary%20that%20was%20sold%20off%20in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattletimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fboeing-aerospace%2Finside-boeings-factory-lapses-that-led-to-alaska-air-blowout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20because%20the%20part%20737MAX9%20fuselage%20is%20shipped%20in%20whole%2C%20mechanics%20at%20Boeing%20rarely%20work%20on%20the%20plug%20doors.%20When%20the%20plug%20door%20frame%20had%20to%20be%20repaired%20and%20the%20plug%20door%20replaced%2C%20two%20separate%20groups%20of%20mechanics%20working%20on%20the%20door%20made%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20a%20plug%20door%20malfunctioned%2C%20and%20Boeing's%20reputation%20was%20damaged%20alongside%20it%2C%20causing%20the%20FAA%20to%20increase%20its%20oversight%20of%20737MAX9%20planes'%20production%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20always%20disappointing%20when%20the%20company%20you%20worked%20for%20makes%20major%20news%20headlines%20for%20a%20mistake.%20However%2C%20it%20doesn't%20change%20my%20general%20opinion%20of%20Boeing.%20I%20know%20there%20are%20many%20dedicated%20employees%20who%20are%20committed%20to%20doing%20their%20jobs%20properly%20and%20safely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220d21d89-9cc8-493f-a068-6fba2379f63d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoeing%20is%20taking%20baby%20steps%20in%20the%20right%20direction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20know%20some%20Boeing%20employees%20and%20followed%20the%20recent%20strike.%20I%20think%20employees%20have%20gotten%20a%20good%20package%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20get%20a%20return%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-workers-approve-labor-contract-end-strike-2024-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUnionized%2520Boeing%2520workers%2520on%2520Monday%2Cbonus%2520for%2520ratifying%2520the%2520contract.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegacy%20defined-benefit%20pension%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20I%20retired%2C%20I%20still%20benefited%20from%20the%20traditional%20pension%20plan%20and%20also%20had%20a%20401(k).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202014%2C%20Boeing%20promised%20employees%20that%20they'd%20build%20the%20777-9%20in%20Washington.%20Part%20of%20the%20strike%20package%20is%20also%20building%20the%20next%20new%20plane%20in%20Washington.%20These%20promises%20show%20that%20Boeing%20management%20is%20waking%20up%20to%20the%20matter%20of%20outsourcing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20is%20also%20bringing%20Spirit%20AeroSystems%2C%20which%20it%20sold%20in%202005%2C%20back%20in-house.%20All%20the%20workers%20will%20be%20merged%20back%20under%20one%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lines%20of%20communication%20between%20two%20in-house%20teams%20are%20often%20simpler%20and%20more%20direct%20than%20with%20a%20supplier.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EWhen%20I%20was%20on%20the%20777%20program%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20I%20would%20call%20my%20counterparts%20at%20the%20Wichita%20site%20to%20resolve%20issues%20and%20exchange%20information.%20I%20couldn't%20do%20this%20with%20a%20supplier%20because%20all%20communication%20had%20to%20be%20through%20supply%20chain%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20shows%20Boeing%20acknowledging%20it%20went%20down%20a%20bad%20path%20when%20it%20sold%20the%20supplier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20see%20these%20actions%20as%20baby%20steps%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20Kelly%20Ortberg%2C%20Boeing's%20CEO%2C%20is%20trying%20to%20steer%20the%20company%20on%20a%20new%20course%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEditor's%20note%3A%20In%20response%20to%20Business%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20Boeing%20spokesperson%20highlighted%20remarks%20by%20CEO%20Kelly%20Ortberg%20during%20the%20company's%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fboeing.mediaroom.com%2Fnews-releases-statements%3Fitem%3D131499%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ethird%20quarter%20report%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BMuch%20has%20been%20written%20about%20how%20we%20got%20to%20where%20we%20are%2C%20but%20most%20also%20recognize%20that%20Boeing%20was%20once%20a%20benchmark%20for%20what%20good%20culture%20looks%20like.%20And%20I%20believe%20we%20can%20return%20to%20that%20legacy.%20I%20know%20culture%20change%20starts%20at%20the%20top.%20Our%20leaders%2C%20from%20me%20on%20down%2C%20need%20to%20be%20closely%20integrated%20with%20our%20business%20and%20the%20people%20who%20are%20doing%20the%20design%20and%20production%20of%20our%20products.%20We%20need%20to%20be%20on%20the%20factory%20floors%2C%20in%20the%20back%20shops%2C%20and%20in%20our%20engineering%20labs.%20We%20need%20to%20know%20what's%20going%20on%2C%20not%20only%20with%20our%20products%20but%20with%20our%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-at-boeing-30-years-outscourcing-problems-787-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736159204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-at-boeing-30-years-outscourcing-problems-787-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Douglas%20Dorsey%20worked%20on%20the%20shop%20floor%20at%20Boeing%20as%20an%20engineer%20for%20over%2030%20years.%20He%20said%20problems%20began%20in%20the%20late%201990s%20during%20a%20merger.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ccheong%40insider.com%20(Charissa%20Cheong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Klarna's%20CEO%20says%20AI%20is%20capable%20of%20doing%20his%20job%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20it%20makes%20him%20feel%20'gloomy'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224974%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Klarna%20CEO%20Sebastian%20Siemiatkowski%20wearing%20a%20gray%20tshirt%20and%20blue%20jeans%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677b9d8859d276c1cdb019ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223316%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKlarna%20CEO%20Sebastian%20Siemiatkowski%20said%20AI%20has%20the%20building%20blocks%20to%20replicate%20today's%20jobs.%3Cp%3ENoam%20Galai%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20TechCrunch%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKlarna%20CEO%20Sebastian%20Siemiatkowski%20says%20AI%20can%20perform%20his%20job%20as%20it%20has%20reasoning%20capabilities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20buy-now%2C%20pay-later%20firm's%20cofounder%20said%20the%20realization%20made%20him%20feel%20%26quot%3Bgloomy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESiemiatkowski%20previously%20said%20Klarna%20stopped%20hiring%20because%20AI%20%26quot%3Bcan%20already%20do%20all%20the%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-ceo-explains-why-its-important-to-promote-internally-jobs-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESebastian%20Siemiatkowski%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20said%20AI%20is%20capable%20of%20performing%20his%20job%20as%20CEO%20of%20Klarna%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he's%20not%20thrilled%20about%20the%20prospect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cofounder%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-stock-trading-robinhood-bnpl-app-ipo-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy-now%2C%20pay-later%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fklarnaseb%2Fstatus%2F1876093526280171699%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%2C%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20capable%20of%20doing%20all%20our%20jobs%2C%20my%20own%20included%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20now%20has%20reasoning%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20necessarily%20super%20excited%20about%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20contrary%20my%20work%20to%20me%20is%20a%20super%20important%20part%20of%20who%20I%20am%2C%20and%20realizing%20it%20might%20become%20unnecessary%20is%20gloomy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiemiatkowski%20explained%20that%20AI%20can%20already%20routinely%20solve%20simple%20problems%20using%20basic%20reasoning.%20Because%20complex%20problems%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bdivided%20into%20smaller%20and%20more%20basic%20reasoning%20tasks%20that%20are%20combined%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20building%20blocks%20for%20AI%20solving%20advanced%20tasks%20already%20exist%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20how%20exactly%20we%20will%20combine%20those%20building%20blocks%20of%20reason%20and%20knowledge%20to%20replicate%20the%20work%20we%20do%20today%20is%20not%20yet%20entirely%20solved%2C%26quot%3B%20Siemiatkowski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20Siemiatkowski%20has%20voiced%20concerns%20about%20AI's%20potential%20to%20disrupt%20traditional%20roles.%20Siemiatkowski%20told%20Bloomberg%20in%20December%20that%20he%20believed%20AI%20could%20%26quot%3Balready%20do%20all%20of%20the%20jobs%20that%20we%20as%20humans%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKlarna%20itself%20has%20embraced%20AI.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20Swedish%20company%20said%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.klarna.com%2Finternational%2Fpress%2Fklarna-ai-assistant-handles-two-thirds-of-customer-service-chats-in-its-first-month%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20assistant%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20%26quot%3Bdoing%20the%20equivalent%20work%26quot%3B%20of%20700%20full-time%20human%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Klarna%20chief%20has%20also%20been%20outspoken%20about%20the%20firm's%20use%20of%20AI%20and%20how%20it's%20impacted%20the%20workforce.%20In%20August%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fklarnaseb%2Fstatus%2F1828684170815836176%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BAI%20allows%20us%20to%20be%20fewer%20in%20total.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20Siemiatkowski%20appeared%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BGrit%26quot%3B%20podcast%20and%20said%20that%20Klarna%20%26quot%3Bstopped%20hiring%20due%20to%20AI%2C%20so%20we're%20shrinking%20because%20we%20have%20a%20natural%20attrition%20rate%20of%2020%25.%26quot%3B%20He%20later%20clarified%20that%20Klarna%20continues%20to%20hire%20some%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20fintech%20company%20has%20been%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-ipo-us-files-buy-now-pay-later-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20gearing%20up%20for%20an%20IPO%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20November%2C%20it%20announced%20it%20confidentially%20submitted%20draft%20registration%20documents%20to%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20month%20the%20company%20told%20its%20employees%20it%20would%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fklarna-alcohol-drug-testing-workers-sweden-ipo-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erandom%20drug%20testing%20for%20staff%20in%20Sweden%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20January.%20Its%20director%20of%20people%20and%20HR%2C%20Mikae